2. Which software development approach is the best?

Though there are a lot of different methodologies, there isn't a universal solution suitable for every project; each of them has its own pros and cons. Choosing a project management strategy that fits best depends on your team structure and experience, the project goals and requirements, budget, and many other factors.

3. What are the most common software development models?

According to statistics, the most popular software development methodologies are Agile (61.5%), Scrum (21.3%), and Waterfall (9.6%). Plus, 5.8% of companies use different models in order to achieve their goals.

4. Why is it necessary to use SDLC methodologies?

Because software development methodologies help to standardize and manage the project, keep things up to a certain standard, and see what is going on both from the client and the team perspective.
